commit.message:
Properly retry failing HTTP requests without JSON response body (#226)

From the Google Cloud documentation: "Error responses usually include a
JSON document in the response body, which contains information about the
error." So far the code only handled exceptions with a JSON body -
otherwise a RuntimeError was thrown. Now the reply is wrapped into a
HttpError.
The missing body was seen in the wild for a 503 response.

Additionally, 408-"Request Timout" is added as additional retryable
status code.

The explicit RateLimitException is removed. It made the logic more
complex for no apparent benefit.
